
Overview of verb espouse

The verb espouse has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (3) adopt, follow, espouse -- (choose and follow; as of theories, ideas, policies, strategies or plans; "She followed the feminist movement"; "The candidate espouses Republican ideals")
2. marry, get married, wed, conjoin, hook up with, get hitched with, espouse -- (take in marriage)
3. espouse, embrace, adopt, sweep up -- (take up the cause, ideology, practice, method, of someone and use it as one's own; "She embraced Catholicism"; "They adopted the Jewish faith")
